### ========================================
### TESTING NOTES
### ========================================
#
# 1. Start your Phoenix server: mix phx.server
# 2. Make sure PostGIS database is running
# 3. Test endpoints in order to understand the API
# 4. Check response headers and status codes
# 5. Verify GeoJSON structure compliance
# 6. Test error handling with invalid parameters
# 7. Monitor response times for performance
# 8. Check pagination links in responses
#
# Expected Results:
# - Basic search: Should return 714 items total
# - Collections: Should return 140 collections
# - Bbox queries: Should filter by spatial extent
# - Datetime queries: Should filter by temporal range
# - Collection filters: Should filter by collection ID
# - Combined queries: Should apply multiple filters
# - Pagination: Should work with limit/offset
# - Error handling: Should return proper error responses
#
# Issues to Watch For:
# - PostGIS errors with intersects queries
# - JSON serialization errors
# - Incorrect GeoJSON geometry formats
